citeinfo.title: Eastern Turkey in Asia. Resafe, sheet 44a. Series G.S.G.S. no. 1522.
citeinfo.othercit: Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Some sheets from this set were revised and issued by War Office. Geographical Section. General Staff, published as G.S.G.S. no. 1522, 1522a. Series covers Mesopotamia and eastern Anatolian parts of Ottoman Empire. "Compiled for the Geographical Section, General Staff, War Office, by Lieut. Col. F.R. Maunsell, C.M.G. [from] 'Vom Mittelmeere zum Persischen Golf' by Max Freiherr von Oppenhim, 1893, Saare & Herzfeld Archeologische Reise im Euphrat u. Tigris Gebeit, 1908, Ostrup Hist. Topogr: Bedrag til Kendskabet til den synske Orken, 1893, Capt. M. Sykes, 1899." With Glossary. Set complete, see index.

descript.abstract: This is a map of the area surrounding the city of Resafe, Syria, shown at a 1:250,000 or 1.014 in. to 4 mi. scale. The map was created for use by Great Britain's War Office.
descript.purpose: The purpose is to view the map in digital format.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows 2000 Version 5.0 (Build 2195) Service Pack 2; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.0.0.535

procstep.procdesc: This map was scanned with a Chroma Tx 40 Plus Wide Format color scanner and WIDEimage 2.8 software at 400 DPI in 24-bit color. The image was then reduced to 256 colors and saved in a TIFF file format. Later the TIFF image was compressed by the Mapping Science GeoJP2 software version 1.04.02. The compression ratio was 10:1.
